{
  "url": "https://www.hymnal.net/cn/hymn/h/488",
  "title": "Lord, Thou hast shown the mystery",
  "verses": [
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "D",
              "text": "Lord, Thou"
            },
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "hast shown the"
            },
            {
              "chord": "A",
              "text": "mys"
            },
            {
              "chord": "A7",
              "text": "te"
            },
            {
              "chord": "D",
              "text": "ry,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "How on the Cross I died with"
            },
            {
              "chord": "A",
              "text": "Thee;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "D",
              "text": "I need"
            },
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "no other"
            },
            {
              "chord": "A",
              "text": "pow'r"
            },
            {
              "chord": "A7",
              "text": "or"
            },
            {
              "chord": "D",
              "text": "way"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "That I may triumph"
            },
            {
              "chord": "A",
              "text": "day"
            },
            {
              "chord": "A7",
              "text": "by"
            },
            {
              "chord": "D",
              "text": "day."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "That cross of Thine is also mine,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Into my life its light doth shine;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "When I believe I'm dead with Thee,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "The world has lost its pow'r o'er me."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Since I am crucified with Thee,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "From sin and self I am set free;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "How can I still enjoy the world"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Or seek its vanities unfurled?"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I take my place, dear Lord, with Thee"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Upon the cross of Calvary."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Thy life and power then are mine,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Since Thou and I in oneness twine."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Since Thou didst come to slay the foe,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "His work and power to overthrow,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I too can overcome in Thee"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And prove Thy mighty pow'r in me."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Yet, for the vict'ry we rely"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Upon the death which Thou didst die;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "We tread the path which Thou hast trod"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Until we reach the goal in God."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "My death with Thee I now believe"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And all its meaning would receive."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Thy death more deeply show to me,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "That from my flesh I may be free."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I long to win as Thou hast won,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "To reign with Thee when Thou dost come."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "If we the cross will gladly bear,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Then in Thy glory we will share."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
